profile_positions.description:
Responsibilities: Producing and planning strategic operating plans and objectives for the long-term future, initiating, leading and directing short term targets, acquisition, producing annual accounts, maintaining control of complete transactions, setting out financial targets and budgets, matchmaking between a range of stakeholders as design companies, artist, academies and vocational training centers.

The Model City Foundation exists to:
* Theorise future alternative living strategies and translate them to physical models to explore spatial, environmental, economic and social qualities, potentials and limitations;
* Promote awareness of the design community and strengthen the role of the designer;
* Challenge and stimulate cross disciplinary research and design processes;
* Cultivate a new breed of designer equipped and skilled to shape desirable futures;
* Strengthen ties between educational and science programs, institutions, government and practices.
* Set an international agenda for research, design and innovation for what the society is, in particular what the city, the natural landscape, its products and lifestyles, architectures, ecologies and economies, networks and infrastructures, could be; a model for the next to come.
